24/12/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- The European Commission (EC) has approved a strategic document to guarantee financial support of over 60m euros for Albania's pro-EU reforms, the EC office in Tirana announced on Tuesday (December 23rd).
The programme aims to assist political and economic reforms as well as the country's efforts to meet EU standards.
The EC will allocate 90.6% of the funds, with donors chipping in the rest.
(Top Channel, EC Tirana official site, Top News, News 24 - 24/12/08)
